    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER - FRONT COVER</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>FRONT COVER</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the front cover as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install a new gasket over the front plate. Hold the gasket in place using the
                        locating dowel pins and grease, as required.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the front cover on the locating dowel pins and install the mounting
                        hardware.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the front cover mounting bolts to the standard torque. See Appendix.</para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>If required, trim the excess material from the bottom of the front cover.</para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the oil pickup tube and oil pan using new gaskets. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="e415_E41507.xml" xrefid="e41507">VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS,
                        FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the oil pump assembly with a new front seal. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="e415_E41509.xml" xrefid="e41509">LUBRICATING OIL PIMP, OIL FILTERS AND
                        COOLER</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the vibration damper, see
                    <hotlnk document="e415_E41507.xml" xrefid="e41507">VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS,
                        FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Be sure the oil pickup tube mounting bolts are installed prior to installing the vibration
                            damper.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the water pump using a new gasket. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="e415_E41510.xml" xrefid="e41510">WATER PUMP AND THERMOSTAT</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the water pump to thermostat housing bypass hose.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
